<text id="02-output-contract" title="Steerco Meeting Playbook Output Contract" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="800" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema (draft-07) for the spec artefact this methodology produces. The validator script enforces the schema.</summary>

  <section title="Schema">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/steerco-meeting-playbook.json",
  "title": "Steerco Meeting Playbook",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "__faion_header__",
    "artefact_path",
    "sections"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "__faion_header__": {
      "type": "object",
      "required": [
        "methodology",
        "version",
        "produces",
        "rules_satisfied"
      ],
      "properties": {
        "methodology": {
          "const": "steerco-meeting-playbook"
        },
        "version": {
          "const": "1.1.0"
        },
        "produces": {
          "const": "spec"
        },
        "rules_satisfied": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "enum": [
              "preread-3-days-early",
              "ask-list-binary",
              "cancel-if-no-decisions",
              "decision-memo-48h",
              "asks-not-status-time-split"
            ]
          },
          "minItems": 1
        }
      }
    },
    "artefact_path": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "sections": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "id",
          "title"
        ]
      },
      "minItems": 1
    }
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <list>
      <item>Missing __faion_header__ block — every artefact MUST carry methodology, version, produces, rules_satisfied.</item>
      <item>rules_satisfied containing IDs outside the steerco-meeting-playbook rule set.</item>
      <item>Empty top-level body (no sections / data / entries / items / criteria) — the artefact must carry payload, not metadata only.</item>
      <item>Free-form prose substituted for the typed sub-fields the schema requires.</item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <example valid="true">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "__faion_header__": {
    "methodology": "steerco-meeting-playbook",
    "version": "1.1.0",
    "produces": "spec",
    "rules_satisfied": [
      "preread-3-days-early",
      "ask-list-binary",
      "cancel-if-no-decisions"
    ]
  },
  "artefact_path": "docs/steerco-meeting-playbook.md",
  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "S1",
      "title": "Scope"
    },
    {
      "id": "S2",
      "title": "Deliverables"
    }
  ]
}
]]></code>
    <note>Header carries methodology + version + produces + rules_satisfied; body matches the per-produces shape.</note>
  </example>

  <example valid="false">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "artefact_path": "docs/steerco-meeting-playbook.md"
}
]]></code>
    <note>Header missing → validator rejects; rules_satisfied not declared → no audit trail.</note>
  </example>

  <reference path="scripts/validate-steerco-meeting-playbook.py">Validator script</reference>
</text>
